<h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
<p class="updated">Last updated: June 11, 2026</p>

<h2>Overview</h2>
<p>Neural NeXus ("we," "our") operates the website neuralnexus.press, including the daily word games, the Daily Brain Check, and the Cognitive Performance Dashboard. This policy describes how we collect, use, and protect your information.</p>

<h2>Daily Games</h2>
<p>Our free daily games (Spelling Bee, Wordie, Mini Crossword, Connections, Contexto, Brain Check) are designed to collect as little as possible:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Leaderboards:</strong> If you submit a score, we store the nickname you enter along with your score, solve time, or guess count in a SQLite database on our server. There are no accounts and no email addresses attached to leaderboard entries.</li>
<li><strong>Game progress and streaks:</strong> Your puzzle progress, stats, and streaks are stored in your browser's localStorage. This data stays on your device and is never sent to our servers.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Analytics</h2>
<p>We use Google Analytics 4 for anonymous traffic measurement, such as which pages are visited and how often. We do not use this data to identify individual visitors.</p>

<h2>Newsletter</h2>
<p>If you enter your email in a subscribe box, it is sent to Substack, our newsletter provider, to sign you up for the Neural NeXus newsletter. We do not store your email on this site. Substack's own <a href="https://substack.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">privacy policy</a> applies to that data.</p>

<h2>Cognitive Performance Dashboard</h2>
<p>The Cognitive Performance Dashboard is a private, password-protected tool. When you use it or connect third-party services, we may collect:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Cognitive test results:</strong> Scores, response times, and session data from tests you voluntarily take (N-Back, PVT, DSST)</li>
<li><strong>Chess.com data:</strong> Publicly available rating information from the Chess.com API</li>
<li><strong>WHOOP data:</strong> If you authorize our application, we access sleep metrics, recovery scores, heart rate variability, and related biometric data through the WHOOP API. We only request read access to sleep, recovery, and cycle data.</li>
<li><strong>Self-reported data:</strong> Subjective ratings (energy, focus, sleep hours) that you voluntarily provide</li>
<li><strong>Supplement tracking:</strong> Supplement names and start dates that you voluntarily enter</li>
</ul>

<h2>How We Use Your Information</h2>
<ul>
<li>To display game leaderboards and live benchmarks</li>
<li>To display your personal cognitive performance trends and analytics</li>
<li>To correlate biometric data with cognitive test results for your personal insight</li>
<li>To track longitudinal changes in cognitive performance</li>
</ul>
<p>We do not sell, share, or distribute your personal data to any third parties.</p>

<h2>Data Storage and Security</h2>
<p>Leaderboard entries and dashboard data are stored in databases on our servers. Access to the cognitive dashboard requires authentication. WHOOP API tokens are stored securely and are never exposed to the client.</p>

<h2>Third-Party Services</h2>
<p>We integrate with the following services:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Substack:</strong> Handles newsletter subscriptions and delivery. Emails you submit in subscribe boxes go directly to Substack.</li>
<li><strong>Google Analytics:</strong> We use GA4 for anonymous website usage analytics.</li>
<li><strong>WHOOP:</strong> We access your data via the WHOOP Developer API using OAuth 2.0. You can revoke access at any time through your WHOOP app settings.</li>
<li><strong>Chess.com:</strong> We access publicly available player statistics through the Chess.com Public API.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Data Retention</h2>
<p>Leaderboard entries are retained to power the game archives and historical leaderboards. Cognitive test data and biometric data are retained indefinitely for longitudinal tracking purposes. You may request deletion of your data at any time by contacting us.</p>

<h2>Your Rights</h2>
<ul>
<li>You can clear your game progress and streaks at any time by clearing your browser's localStorage</li>
<li>You can disconnect WHOOP access at any time via the WHOOP app</li>
<li>You can request export of all your data (CSV or JSON) from the dashboard</li>
<li>You can request deletion of your data by contacting us</li>
</ul>

<h2>Contact</h2>
<p>For questions about this privacy policy, contact: <a href="mailto:davemkingsley@gmail.com">davemkingsley@gmail.com</a></p>
